Security Events from the Text:
1. A missile splashed down in the waters of the Red Sea;
2. A commercial vessel was reportedly not damaged by a missile that was splashed down in the waters of the Red Sea;
3. The United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations center reported that the attack happened near the crucial Bab el-Mandeb Strait;
4. Shipping through the Red Sea and Gulf of Aden has been in decline due to the threat of sabotage bombs, mines, and alleged weapons shipments.
